jobs.prompt:
You are working in Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/. The app is React + Vite + TypeScript.

Create the module infrastructure — the registry and hooks that all quadrant modules will use.

Create these files:

1. src/modules/types.ts:
```typescript
export interface QuadrantProps {
  quadrantId: string;
  span: { cols: number; rows: number };
  config?: Record<string, unknown>;
}

export interface ModuleDefinition {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  type: 'display' | 'input' | 'tool' | 'composite';
  defaultSpan: string;
  component: React.ComponentType<QuadrantProps>;
  description: string;
}
```

2. src/modules/moduleRegistry.ts:
- Same pattern as src/primitives/registry.ts (which already exists — follow that pattern exactly)
- Map<string, ModuleDefinition>
- registerModule(def: ModuleDefinition): void
- resolveModule(id: string): ModuleDefinition | undefined
- listModules(): ModuleDefinition[]

3. src/hooks/useModuleData.ts:
```typescript
export function useModuleData<T>(endpoint: string, options?: { refreshInterval?: number; enabled?: boolean }): {
  data: T | null;
  loading: boolean;
  error: string | null;
  refetch: () => void;
}
```
- Uses fetch to call /api/* endpoints
- Optional polling via setInterval (cleanup on unmount)
- Returns { data, loading, error, refetch }
- enabled flag to conditionally fetch (default true)

4. src/modules/index.ts:
- Empty barrel file for now with a comment: // Module registrations will be added here
- Export { registerModule, resolveModule, listModules } from moduleRegistry

Write all files. Verify they compile.
